This is for spinning up a new EC2 machine and web server in it.

Pre-requisites:
1. Terraform installed
2. AWS Account created
3. AWS User created with below policies configured.

AmazonEC2FullAccess
AmazonS3FullAccess
AmazonDynamoDBFullAccess
AmazonRDSFullAccess
CloudWatchFullAccess
IAMFullAccess

4. AWS Access Key Id and AWS Secret configured as environment variables

$ export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxx
$ export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxx

5. Run terraform commands

$ terraform init
$ terraform plan
$ terraform apply

Outputs:

public_ip = "3.131.141.97"

6. Test

$ curl http://3.131.141.97:8080
Hello, world!
